#' @name FilterPanelAPI
2 
#' @docType class
3 
#'
4 
#' @title Class to encapsulate the API of the filter panel of a teal app
5 
#'
6 
#' @details
7 
#'   The purpose of this class is to encapsulate the API of the filter panel in a new class `FilterPanelAPI` so
8 
#'   that it can be passed and used in the `server` call of any module instead of passing the whole `FilteredData`
9 
#'   object.
10 
#'
11 
#'   This class is supported by methods to set, get, remove filter states in the filter panel API.
12 
#'
13 
#' @export
14 
#'
15 
#' @examples
16 
#' library(teal.slice)
17 
#' fd <- teal.slice::init_filtered_data(list(iris = list(dataset = iris)))
18 
#' fpa <- FilterPanelAPI$new(fd)
19 
#'
20 
#' # get the actual filter state --> empty named list
21 
#' isolate(fpa$get_filter_state())
22 
#'
23 
#' # set a filter state
24 
#' set_filter_state(
25 
#'   fpa,
26 
#'   filter_settings(
27 
#'     filter_var(dataname = "iris", varname = "Species", selected = "setosa", keep_na = TRUE)
28 
#'   )
29 
#' )
30 
#'
31 
#' # get the actual filter state --> named list with filters
32 
#' isolate(fpa$get_filter_state())
33 
#'
34 
#' # remove all_filter_states
35 
#' fpa$clear_filter_states()
36 
#'
37 
#' # get the actual filter state --> empty named list
38 
#' isolate(fpa$get_filter_state())
39 
#'

#' Initialize a `FilterStateExpr` object

                    		
                  

                  

                    387
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    388
                    
                    
                      
#' Initialize a `FilterStateExpr` object

                    		
                  

                  

                    389
                    
                    
                      
#' @param id (`character(1)`)\cr

                    		
                  

                  

                    390
                    
                    
                      
#'   identifier of the filter

                    		
                  

                  

                    391
                    
                    
                      
#' @param title (`character(1)`)\cr

                    		
                  

                  

                    392
                    
                    
                      
#'   title of the filter

                    		
                  

                  

                    393
                    
                    
                      
#' @param dataname (`character(1)`)\cr

                    		
                  

                  

                    394
                    
                    
                      
#'   name of the dataset where `expr` could be executed on.

                    		
                  

                  

                    395
                    
                    
                      
#' @param expr (`character(1)`)\cr

                    		
                  

                  

                    396
                    
                    
                      
#'   logical expression written in executable way. By "executable" means

                    		
                  

                  

                    397
                    
                    
                      
#'   that `subset` call should be able to evaluate this without failure. For

                    		
                  

                  

                    398
                    
                    
                      
#'   example `MultiAssayExperiment::subsetByColData` requires variable names prefixed

                    		
                  

                  

                    399
                    
                    
                      
#'   by dataname (e.g. `data$var1 == "x" & data$var2 > 0`). For `data.frame` call

                    		
                  

                  

                    400
                    
                    
                      
#'   can be written without prefixing `var1 == "x" & var2 > 0`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    401
                    
                    
                      
#' @param disabled (`logical(1)`)\cr

                    		
                  

                  

                    402
                    
                    
                      
#'   flag specifying whether the `FilterState` is initiated disabled

                    		
                  

                  

                    403
                    
                    
                      
#' @param ... additional arguments to be saved as a list in `private$extras` field

                    		
                  

                  

                    404
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    405
                    
                    
                      
#' @return `FilterStateExpr` object

                    		
                  

                  

                    406
                    
                    
                      
#' @keywords internal

                    		
                  

                  

                    407

#' Check that a given range is valid

                    		
                  

                  

                    412
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    413
                    
                    
                      
#' @param subinterval (`numeric` or `date`)\cr vector of length 2 to be compared against the full range.

                    		
                  

                  

                    414
                    
                    
                      
#' @param range (`numeric` or `date`)\cr vector of length 2 containing the full range to validate against.

                    		
                  

                  

                    415
                    
                    
                      
#' @param pre_msg `character` message to print before error for additional context.

                    		
                  

                  

                    416
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    417
                    
                    
                      
#' @return `NULL` if `subinterval` is a valid range or error with message otherwise.

                    		
                  

                  

                    418
                    
                    
                      
#' @keywords internal

                    		
                  

                  

                    419
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    420
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    421
                    
                    
                      
#' \dontrun{

                    		
                  

                  

                    422
                    
                    
                      
#' teal.slice:::check_in_range(c(3, 1), c(1, 3))

                    		
                  

                  

                    423
                    
                    
                      
#' teal.slice:::check_in_range(c(0, 3), c(1, 3))

                    		
                  

                  

                    424
                    
                    
                      
#' teal.slice:::check_in_range(

                    		
                  

                  

                    425
                    
                    
                      
#'   c(as.Date("2020-01-01"), as.Date("2020-01-20")),

                    		
                  

                  

                    426
                    
                    
                      
#'   c(as.Date("2020-01-01"), as.Date("2020-01-02"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    427
                    
                    
                      
#' )

                    		
                  

                  

                    428
                    
                    
                      
#' }

                    		
                  

                  

                    429
                    
                    
                      
check_in_range <- function(subinterval, range, pre_msg = "") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    430
                    66x
                    
                      
  epsilon <- .Machine$double.eps^0.5 # needed for floating point arithmetic; same value as in base::all.equal()

                    		
                  

                  

                    431
                    66x
                    
                      
  if ((length(subinterval) != 2)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    432
                    2x
                    
                      
    stop(

                    		
                  

                  

                    433
                    2x
                    
                      
      sprintf(

                    		
                  

                  

                    434
                    2x
                    
                      
        "%s range length should be 2 while it is %s",

                    		
                  

                  

                    435
                    2x
                    
                      
        pre_msg,

                    		
                  

                  

                    436
                    2x
                    
                      
        length(subinterval)

                    		
                  

                  

                    437
                    
                    
                      
      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    438
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    439
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    440
                    64x
                    
                      
  if (subinterval[[2]] + epsilon < subinterval[[1]]) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    441
                    1x
                    
                      
    stop(sprintf(

                    		
                  

                  

                    442
                    1x
                    
                      
      "%s unexpected: the upper bound of the range lower than the lower bound \n %s < %s",

                    		
                  

                  

                    443
                    1x
                    
                      
      pre_msg,

                    		
                  

                  

                    444
                    1x
                    
                      
      subinterval[[2]],

                    		
                  

                  

                    445
                    1x
                    
                      
      subinterval[[1]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    446
                    
                    
                      
    ))

                    		
                  

                  

                    447
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    448
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    449
                    63x
                    
                      
  if ((subinterval[[1]] + epsilon < range[[1]]) || (subinterval[[2]] - epsilon > range[[2]])) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    450
                    1x
                    
                      
    stop(

                    		
                  

                  

                    451
                    1x
                    
                      
      sprintf(

                    		
                  

                  

                    452
                    1x
                    
                      
        "%s range (%s) not valid for full range (%s)",

                    		
                  

                  

                    453
                    1x
                    
                      
        pre_msg, toString(subinterval), toString(range)

                    		
                  

                  

                    454
                    
                    
                      
      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    455
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    456
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    457
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    458

#' Check that one set is a subset of another

#' Raises an error message if not and says which elements are not in the allowed `choices`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    462
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    463
                    
                    
                      
#' @param subset,choices atomic vectors

                    		
                  

                  

                    464
                    
                    
                      
#' @param pre_msg `character` message to print before error should there be any errors

                    		
                  

                  

                    465
                    
                    
                      
#' @keywords internal

                    		
                  

                  

                    466

#' Find containing limits for interval.

                    		
                  

                  

                    496
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    497
                    
                    
                      
#' Given an interval and a numeric vector,

                    		
                  

                  

                    498
                    
                    
                      
#' find the smallest interval within the numeric vector that contains the interval.

                    		
                  

                  

                    499
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    500
                    
                    
                      
#' This is a helper function for `RangeFilterState` that modifies slider selection

                    		
                  

                  

                    501
                    
                    
                      
#' so that the _subsetting call_ includes the value specified by the filter API call.

                    		
                  

                  

                    502
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    503
                    
                    
                      
#' Regardless of the underlying numeric data, the slider always presents 100 steps.

                    		
                  

                  

                    504
                    
                    
                      
#' The ticks on the slider do not represent actual observations but rather borders between virtual bins.

                    		
                  

                  

                    505
                    
                    
                      
#' Since the value selected on the slider is passed to `private$selected` and that in turn

                    		
                  

                  

                    506
                    
                    
                      
#' updates the slider selection, programmatic selection of arbitrary values may inadvertently shift

                    		
                  

                  

                    507
                    
                    
                      
#' the selection to the closest tick, thereby dropping the actual value set (if it exists in the data).

                    		
                  

                  

                    508
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    509
                    
                    
                      
#' This function purposely shifts the selection to the closest ticks whose values form an interval

                    		
                  

                  

                    510
                    
                    
                      
#' that will contain the interval defined by the filter API call.

                    		
                  

                  

                    511
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    512
                    
                    
                      
#' @param x `numeric(2)` interval to contain

                    		
                  

                  

                    513
                    
                    
                      
#' @param range `numeric(>=2)` vector of values to contain `x` in

                    		
                  

                  

                    514
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    515
                    
                    
                      
#' @return Numeric vector of length 2 that lies within `range`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    516
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    517
                    
                    
                      
#' @keywords internal

                    		
                  

                  

                    518
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    519
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    520
                    
                    
                      
#' \donttest{

                    		
                  

                  

                    521
                    
                    
                      
#' ticks <- 1:10

                    		
                  

                  

                    522
                    
                    
                      
#' values1 <- c(3, 5)

                    		
                  

                  

                    523
                    
                    
                      
#' teal.slice:::contain_interval(values1, ticks)

                    		
                  

                  

                    524
                    
                    
                      
#' values2 <- c(3.1, 5.7)

                    		
                  

                  

                    525
                    
                    
                      
#' teal.slice:::contain_interval(values2, ticks)

                    		
                  

                  

                    526
                    
                    
                      
#' values3 <- c(0, 20)

                    		
                  

                  

                    527
                    
                    
                      
#' teal.slice:::contain_interval(values3, ticks)

                    		
                  

                  

                    528
                    
                    
                      
#'}

contain_interval <- function(x, range) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    530
                    146x
                    
                      
  checkmate::assert_numeric(x, len = 2L, any.missing = FALSE, sorted = TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    531
                    141x
                    
                      
  checkmate::assert_numeric(range, min.len = 2L, any.missing = FALSE, sorted = TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    532
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    533
                    137x
                    
                      
  x[1] <- Find(function(i) i <= x[1], range, nomatch = min(range), right = TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    534
                    137x
                    
                      
  x[2] <- Find(function(i) i >= x[2], range, nomatch = max(range))

                    		
                  

                  

                    535
                    137x
                    
                      
  x

                    		
                  

                  

                    536
                    
                    
                      
}

#' Count the number of significant digits in a number.

                    		
                  

                  

                    597
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    598
                    
                    
                      
#' Adapted from https://www.r-bloggers.com/2010/04/significant-figures-in-r-and-info-zeros/

                    		
                  

                  

                    599
                    
                    
                      
#'  The supplied vector should be numbers represented as a character. `NA`, `Inf`,

                    		
                  

                  

                    600
                    
                    
                      
#'  and `-Inf` should be coded as the strings "NA", "Inf", and "-Inf". In these

                    		
                  

                  

                    601
                    
                    
                      
#'  cases, a count of -1 is returned.

                    		
                  

                  

                    602
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    603
                    
                    
                      
#' @param nums A vector of numbers that have been converted to character.

                    		
                  

                  

                    604
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    605
                    
                    
                      
#' @return Vector of `length(nums)` with counts of significant digits.

                    		
                  

                  

                    606
                    
                    
                      
#' @keywords internal

                    		
                  

                  

                    607
                    
                    
                      
#' @noRd

                    		
                  

                  

                    608
                    
                    
                      
n_sig_digits <- function(nums) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    609
                    7x
                    
                      
  checkmate::assert_character(nums, any.missing = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    610
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    611
                    7x
                    
                      
  vapply(nums, FUN.VALUE = numeric(1), USE.NAMES = FALSE, FUN = function(num) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    612
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    613
                    !
                    
                      
    if (grepl("e", num)) return(-1)

                    		
                  

                  

                    614
                    1x
                    
                      
    if (num == "NA") return(-1)

                    		
                  

                  

                    615
                    2x
                    
                      
    if (num == "Inf" || num == "-Inf") return(-1)

                    		
                  

                  

                    616
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    617
                    23x
                    
                      
    sig_digits <- 1

                    		
                  

                  

                    618
                    23x
                    
                      
    i <- 0

                    		
                  

                  

                    619
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    620
                    23x
                    
                      
    if (grepl("\\.", num)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    621
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    622
                    12x
                    
                      
      num_split <- unlist(strsplit(num, "\\."))

                    		
                  

                  

                    623
                    12x
                    
                      
      num_str <- paste(num_split[1], num_split[2], sep = "")

                    		
                  

                  

                    624
                    12x
                    
                      
      current_n_digits <- nchar(num_str)

                    		
                  

                  

                    625
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    626
                    12x
                    
                      
      while (i < current_n_digits) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    627
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    628
                    19x
                    
                      
        if (substr(num_str, i + 1, i + 1) == "0") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    629
                    7x
                    
                      
          i <- i + 1

                    		
                  

                  

                    630
                    7x
                    
                      
          next

                    		
                  

                  

                    631
                    
                    
                      
        } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    632
                    12x
                    
                      
          sig_digits <- current_n_digits - i

                    		
                  

                  

                    633
                    12x
                    
                      
          break

                    		
                  

                  

                    634
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    635
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    636
                    
                    
                      
    } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    637
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    638
                    11x
                    
                      
      num_str <- num

                    		
                  

                  

                    639
                    11x
                    
                      
      current_n_digits <- nchar(num_str)

                    		
                  

                  

                    640
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    641
                    11x
                    
                      
      while (i < current_n_digits) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    642
                    17x
                    
                      
        if (substr(num_str, current_n_digits - i, current_n_digits - i) == "0") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    643
                    7x
                    
                      
          i <- i + 1

                    		
                  

                  

                    644
                    7x
                    
                      
          next

                    		
                  

                  

                    645
                    
                    
                      
        } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    646
                    10x
                    
                      
          sig_digits <- current_n_digits - i

                    		
                  

                  

                    647
                    10x
                    
                      
          break

                    		
                  

                  

                    648
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    649
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    650
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    651
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    652
                    23x
                    
                      
    return(sig_digits)

                    		
                  

                  

                    653
                    
                    
                      
  })

                    		
                  

                  

                    654

#' @name FilteredData

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#' @docType class

#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' @title Class to encapsulate filtered datasets

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' @details

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' The main purpose of this class is to provide a collection of reactive datasets,

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' each dataset having a filter state that determines how it is filtered.

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' For each dataset, `get_filter_expr` returns the call to filter the dataset according

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' to the filter state. The data itself can be obtained through `get_data`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' The datasets are filtered lazily, i.e. only when requested / needed in a Shiny app.

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#' By design, any dataname set through `set_dataset` cannot be removed because

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#' other code may already depend on it. As a workaround, the underlying

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' data can be set to `NULL`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#' The class currently supports variables of the following types within datasets:

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#' - `choices`: variable of type `factor`, e.g. `ADSL$COUNTRY`, `iris$Species`

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#'      zero or more options can be selected, when the variable is a factor

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#' - `logical`: variable of type `logical`, e.g. `ADSL$TRT_FLAG`

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#'      exactly one option must be selected, `TRUE` or `FALSE`

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#' - `ranges`: variable of type `numeric`, e.g. `ADSL$AGE`, `iris$Sepal.Length`

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#'      numerical range, a range within this range can be selected

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#' - `dates`: variable of type `Date`, `POSIXlt`

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#' Other variables cannot be used for filtering the data in this class.

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#' Common arguments are:

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
#' 1. `filtered`: whether to return a filtered result or not

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
#' 2. `dataname`: the name of one of the datasets in this `FilteredData`

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
#' 3. `varname`: one of the columns in a dataset

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
#' @keywords internal

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
#' library(shiny)

                    		
                  

                  

                    38

    #' @description

    #' Initialize a `FilterState` object. This class

    #' @description

                    		
                  

                  

                    194
                    
                    
                      
    #' Returns reproducible condition call for current selection.

                    		
                  

                  

                    195
                    
                    
                      
    #' For this class returned call looks like

                    		
                  

                  

                    196
                    
                    
                      
    #' `<varname> >= as.POSIXct(<min>) & <varname> <= <max>)`

                    		
                  

                  

                    197
                    
                    
                      
    #' with optional `is.na(<varname>)`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    198
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param dataname name of data set; defaults to `private$dataname`

                    		
                  

                  

                    199
                    
                    
                      
    #' @return (`call`)

                    		
                  

                  

                    200
                    
                    
                      
    #'

                    		
                  

                  

                    201
                    
                    
                      
    get_call = function(dataname) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    202
                    8x
                    
                      
      if (isFALSE(private$is_any_filtered())) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    203
                    2x
                    
                      
        return(NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    204
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    205
                    4x
                    
                      
      if (missing(dataname)) dataname <- private$dataname

                    		
                  

                  

                    206
                    6x
                    
                      
      choices <- private$get_selected()

                    		
                  

                  

                    207
                    6x
                    
                      
      tzone <- Find(function(x) x != "", attr(as.POSIXlt(choices), "tzone"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    208
                    6x
                    
                      
      class <- class(choices)[1L]

                    		
                  

                  

                    209
                    6x
                    
                      
      date_fun <- as.name(

                    		
                  

                  

                    210
                    6x
                    
                      
        switch(class,

                    		
                  

                  

                    211
                    6x
                    
                      
          "POSIXct" = "as.POSIXct",

                    		
                  

                  

                    212
                    6x
                    
                      
          "POSIXlt" = "as.POSIXlt"

                    		
                  

                  

                    213
                    
                    
                      
        )

                    		
                  

                  

                    214
                    
                    
                      
      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    215
                    6x
                    
                      
      choices <- as.character(choices + c(0, 1))

                    		
                  

                  

                    216
                    6x
                    
                      
      filter_call <-

                    		
                  

                  

                    217
                    6x
                    
                      
        call(

                    		
                  

                  

                    218
                    
                    
                      
          "&",

                    		
                  

                  

                    219
                    6x
                    
                      
          call(

                    		
                  

                  

                    220
                    
                    
                      
            ">=",

                    		
                  

                  

                    221
                    6x
                    
                      
            private$get_varname_prefixed(dataname),

                    		
                  

                  

                    222
                    6x
                    
                      
            as.call(list(date_fun, choices[1L], tz = tzone))

                    		
                  

                  

                    223
                    
                    
                      
          ),

                    		
                  

                  

                    224
                    6x
                    
                      
          call(

                    		
                  

                  

                    225
                    
                    
                      
            "<",

                    		
                  

                  

                    226
                    6x
                    
                      
            private$get_varname_prefixed(dataname),

                    		
                  

                  

                    227
                    6x
                    
                      
            as.call(list(date_fun, choices[2L], tz = tzone))

                    		
                  

                  

                    228
                    
                    
                      
          )

                    		
                  

                  

                    229
                    
                    
                      
        )

                    		
                  

                  

                    230
                    6x
                    
                      
      private$add_keep_na_call(filter_call, dataname)

                    		
                  

                  

                    231
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    232
                    
                    
                      
  ),

                    		
                  

                  

                    233

  # private members ----

    set_choices = function(choices) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    239
                    24x
                    
                      
      if (is.null(choices)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    240
                    21x
                    
                      
        choices <- as.POSIXct(trunc(range(private$x, na.rm = TRUE), units = "secs"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    241
                    
                    
                      
      } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    242
                    3x
                    
                      
        choices <- as.POSIXct(choices, units = "secs")

                    		
                  

                  

                    243
                    3x
                    
                      
        choices_adjusted <- c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    244
                    3x
                    
                      
          max(choices[1L], min(as.POSIXct(private$x), na.rm = TRUE)),

                    		
                  

                  

                    245
                    3x
                    
                      
          min(choices[2L], max(as.POSIXct(private$x), na.rm = TRUE))

                    3x

                    1x
                    
                      
          warning(sprintf(

            "Choices adjusted (some values outside of variable range). Varname: %s, dataname: %s.",

                    		
                  

                  

                    250
                    1x
                    
                      
            private$varname, private$dataname

                    		
                  

                  

                    251

                    252
                    1x
                    
                      
          choices <- choices_adjusted

                    		
                  

                  

                    253
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    254
                    3x
                    
                      
        if (choices[1L] >= choices[2L]) {

                    1x
                    
                      
          warning(sprintf(

                    1x
                    
                      
            "Invalid choices: lower is higher / equal to upper, or not in range of variable values.

            private$varname, private$dataname

                    266
                    24x

    #' @param id (`character(1)`)\cr

                    175

    server = function(id) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    180
                    !
                    
                      
      moduleServer(

                    		
                  

                  

                    181
                    !
                    
                      
        id = id,

                    		
                  

                  

                    182
                    !
                    
                      
        function(input, output, session) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    183
                    !
                    
                      
          private$server_summary("summary")

                    		
                  

                  

                    184
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    185
                    
                    
                      
          # Disable/enable this filter state in response to switch flip.

                    		
                  

                  

                    186
                    !
                    
                      
          private$observers$is_disabled <- observeEvent(input$enable,

                    		
                  

                  

                    187
                    
                    
                      
            {

                    		
                  

                  

                    188
                    !
                    
                      
              if (isTRUE(input$enable)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    189
                    !
                    
                      
                private$disabled(FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    190
                    
                    
                      
              } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    191
                    !
                    
                      
                private$disabled(TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    192
                    
                    
                      
              }

                    		
                  

                  

                    193
                    
                    
                      
            },

                    		
                  

                  

                    194
                    !
                    
                      
            ignoreInit = TRUE

                    		
                  

                  

                    195
                    
                    
                      
          )

                    		
                  

                  

                    196
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    197
                    
                    
                      
          # Update disable switch according to disabled state.

                    		
                  

                  

                    198
                    
                    
                      
          # This is necessary to react to the global disable action.

                    		
                  

                  

                    199
                    !
                    
                      
          private$observers$is_disabled <- observeEvent(private$is_disabled(), {

                    		
                  

                  

                    200
                    !
                    
                      
            if (isTRUE(private$is_disabled())) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    201
                    !
                    
                      
              shinyWidgets::updateSwitchInput(inputId = "enable", value = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    202
                    
                    
                      
            }

                    		
                  

                  

                    203
                    !
                    
                      
            if (isFALSE(private$is_disabled())) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    204
                    !
                    
                      
              shinyWidgets::updateSwitchInput(inputId = "enable", value = TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    205
                    
                    
                      
            }

                    		
                  

                  

                    206
                    
                    
                      
          })

                    		
                  

                  

                    207
                    !
                    
                      
          out <- reactive(input$remove) # back to parent to remove self

                    		
                  

                  

                    208
                    !
                    
                      
          out

                    		
                  

                  

                    209
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    210
                    
                    
                      
      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    211
                    
                    
                      
    },

      private$expr

    }
