)

                    		
                  

                
              

            

            

              

                
                  

                    1
                    
                    
                      
#' Manage filter state(s).

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' Functions for passing filter state information between objects.

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' These functions create and manage filter state specifications.

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' A single filter state can be fully described by a `teal_slice` object and such

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' objects will be used to create, modify, and delete a filter state.

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' A `teal_slice` contains a number of common fields (all named arguments of `filter_var`)

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' but only `dataname` and `varname` are mandatory, while the others have default values.

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' Setting any of the other values to NULL means that these parameters will not be modified

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#' (when setting an existing state) or that they will be determined by data (when creating new a new one).

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' Each of the common fields corresponds to one private field in `FilterState`

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' where it is stored and from where it is retrieved when calling `FiterState$get_state`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#' A `teal_slice` can also contain any number of additional fields, passed to `...`

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' as `name:value` pairs. These are collated into a list and stored in the

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#' `private$extras` field.

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#' All `teal_slice` fields can be passed as arguments to `FilterState` constructors.

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#' A `teal_slice` can be passed to `FilterState$set_state`, which will modify the state.

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#' However, once a `FilterState` is created, only the **mutable** features can be set with a `teal_slice`:

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#' `selected`, `keep_na`, `keep_inf`, and `disabled`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#' Special consideration is given to the `fixed` field. This is always a logical flag that defaults to FALSE.

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#' In a `FilterState` instantiated with `fixed = TRUE` the features `selected`, `keep_na`, `keep_inf`

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#' cannot be changed but the`disabled` can.

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#' `filter_var` creates a `teal_slice` object, which specifies a filter for a single variable,

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
#' passed to and resolved by `FilterState` objects.

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
#' `filter_settings` collates multiple `teal_slice` objects into `teal_slices`,

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
#' a complete filter specification. This is used by all classes above `FilterState`

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
#' as well as `filter_panel_api` wrapper functions.

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
#' `teal_slices` also specifies which variables cannot be filtered

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
#' and how observations are tallied, which is resolved by `FilterStates`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
#' @section Filters in `SumarizedExperiment` and `MultiAssayExperiment` objects:

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
#' To establish a filter on a column in a `data.frame`, `dataname` and `varname` are sufficient.

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
#' Filter states created created for `SummarizedExperiments` require more information

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      
#' as each variable is either located in the `rowData` or `colData` slots.

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      
#' Thus, `teal_slice` objects that refer to such filter states must also contain the field `arg`

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
#' that specifies "subset" for variables in `rowData` and "select" for those in `colData`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      
#' Likewise, observations in a `MultiAssayExpeeiment` can be filtered based on the content of the `colData` slot

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
#' or based on the contents of `rowData` and `colData` of any of its experiments. Hence, another field is necessary.

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      
#' `teal_slice` objects referring to `MultiAssayExperiment` objects must contain the field `datalabel`

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      
#' that names either an experiment (as listed in `experimentList(<MAE>)`) or "subjects"

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    
                    
                      
#' if it refers to the `MultiAssaysExperiment` `colData`. They must **also** specify `arg` as "subset" or "select"

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    
                    
                      
#' for experiments and as "y" for `colData`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    
                    
                      
#' @param dataname `character(1)` name of data set

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    
                    
                      
#' @param varname `character(1)` name of variable

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    
                    
                      
#' @param choices optional vector specifying allowed choices;

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    
                    
                      
#'  possibly a subset of values in data; type and size depends on variable type

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    
                    
                      
#' @param selected optional vector specifying selection;

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    
                    
                      
#'  type and size depends on variable type

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    
                    
                      
#' @param keep_na `logical(1)` or `NULL` optional logical flag specifying whether to keep missing values

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    
                    
                      
#' @param keep_inf `logical(1)` or `NULL` optional logical flag specifying whether to keep infinite values

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    
                    
                      
#' @param fixed `logical(1)` logical flag specifying whether to fix this filter state (i.e. forbid setting state)

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    
                    
                      
#' @param disabled `logical(1)`logical flag specifying whether to disable this filter state

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    
                    
                      
#' @param include_varnames `named list` of `character` vectors where list names match names of data sets

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    
                    
                      
#'  and vector elements match variable names in respective data sets;

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    
                    
                      
#'  specifies which variables are not allowed to be filtered.

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    
                    
                      
#'  Both `include_varnames` and `exclude_varnames` can't be specified for the same dataset in the same call.

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    
                    
                      
#' @param exclude_varnames `named list` of `character` vectors where list names match names of data sets

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    
                    
                      
#'  and vector elements match variable names in respective data sets;

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    
                    
                      
#'  specifies which variables are not allowed to be filtered.

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    
                    
                      
#'  Both `include_varnames` and `exclude_varnames` can't be specified for the same dataset in the same call.

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    
                    
                      
#' @param count_type `character(1)` string specifying how observations are tallied by these filter states.

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    
                    
                      
#'  Possible options:

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    
                    
                      
#'  - `"all"` to have counts of single `FilterState` to show number of observation in filtered

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    
                    
                      
#'   and unfiltered dataset.

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    
                    
                      
#'  - `"none"` to have counts of single `FilterState` to show unfiltered number only.

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    
                    
                      
#' @param id (`character(1)`)\cr

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    
                    
                      
#'   identifier of the filter

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    
                    
                      
#' @param title (`reactive`)\cr

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    
                    
                      
#'   title of the filter (used by `filter_expr`)

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    
                    
                      
#' @param expr (`language`)\cr

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    
                    
                      
#'   logical expression written in executable way. By "executable" means

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    
                    
                      
#'   that `subset` call should be able to evaluate this without failure. For

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    
                    
                      
#'   example `MultiAssayExperiment::subsetByColData` requires variable names prefixed

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    
                    
                      
#'   by dataname (e.g. `data$var1 == "x" & data$var2 > 0`). For `data.frame` call

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    
                    
                      
#'   can be written without prefixing `var1 == "x" & var2 > 0`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    
                    
                      
#' @param disabled (`logical(1)`)\cr

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    
                    
                      
#'   flag specifying whether the `FilterState` is initiated disabled

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    
                    
                      
#' @param ... additional arguments to be saved as a list in `private$extras` field

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    
                    
                      
#' @param show_all `logical(1)` specifying whether NULL elements should also be printed

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    
                    
                      
#' @param tss `teal_slices`

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    
                    
                      
#' @param field `character(1)` name of `teal_slice` element

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    
                    
                      
#' @param ... for `filter_var` any number of additional fields given as `name:value` pairs\cr

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    
                    
                      
#'            for `filter_settings` any number of `teal_slice` objects\cr

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    
                    
                      
#'            for other functions arguments passed to other methods

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    
                    
                      
#' @return

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    
                    
                      
#' `filter_var` returns object of class `teal_slice`, which is a named list.

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    
                    
                      
#' `filter_settings` returns object of class `teal_slices`, which is an unnamed list of `teal_slice` objects.

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    
                    
                      
#' filter_1 <- filter_var("dataname1", "varname1", letters, "b", FALSE, extra1 = "extraone")

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    
                    
                      
#' filter_2 <- filter_var("dataname1", "varname2", 1:10, 2, TRUE, FALSE, extra2 = "extratwo")

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    
                    
                      
#' filter_3 <- filter_var("dataname2", "varname3", 1:10 / 10, 0.2, TRUE, FALSE,

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    
                    
                      
#'   extra1 = "extraone", extra2 = "extratwo"

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    
                    
                      
#' )

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    
                    
                      
#' all_filters <- filter_settings(

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    
                    
                      
#'   filter_1,

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    
                    
                      
#'   filter_2,

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    
                    
                      
#'   filter_3,

                    		
                  

                  

                    109
                    
                    
                      
#'   exclude_varnames = list(

                    		
                  

                  

                    110
                    
                    
                      
#'     "dataname1" = "varname2"

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    
                    
                      
#'   )

                    		
                  

                  

                    112
                    
                    
                      
#' )

                    		
                  

                  

                    113
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    114
                    
                    
                      
#' teal.slice:::slices_which(all_filters, 'dataname == "dataname2"')

                    		
                  

                  

                    115
                    
                    
                      
#' x <- "dataname2"

                    		
                  

                  

                    116
                    
                    
                      
#' teal.slice:::slices_which(all_filters, sprintf('dataname == "%s"', x))

                    		
                  

                  

                    117
                    
                    
                      
#' teal.slice:::slices_field(all_filters, "dataname")

                    		
                  

                  

                    118
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    119
                    
                    
                      
#' @name teal_slice

                    		
                  

                  

                    120
                    
                    
                      
NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    121
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    122
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    123
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    124
                    
                    
                      
#' @rdname teal_slice

#' Ensure the ellipsis, ..., in method arguments are empty

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' Ellipsis, ..., are needed as part of method arguments to allow for its arguments to be different from its generic's

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' arguments and for this to pass check(). Hence, ..., should always be empty. This function will check for this

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' condition.

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' @param ... it should literally just be ...

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' @param stop TRUE to raise an error; FALSE will output warning message

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' @param allowed_args character vector naming arguments that are allowed in the \code{...}.

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#'   to allow for unnamed arguments, let "" be one of the elements in this character vector.

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#' @return \code{NULL} if ... is empty

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' @keywords internal

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' method.class <- function(a, b, c, ...) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#'   check_ellipsis(...)

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#' }

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#' method.class <- function(a, b, c, ...) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#'   check_ellipsis(..., allowed_args = c("y", "z"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#' }

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
check_ellipsis <- function(..., stop = FALSE, allowed_args = character(0)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    18x
                    
                      
  if (!missing(...)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    16x
                    
                      
    checkmate::assert_flag(stop)

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    16x
                    
                      
    checkmate::assert_character(allowed_args, min.len = 0, null.ok = TRUE, any.missing = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    16x
                    
                      
    args <- list(...)

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    16x
                    
                      
    arg_names <- names(args)

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    16x
                    
                      
    if (is.null(arg_names)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    4x
                    
                      
      arg_names <- rep("", length(args))

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    16x
                    
                      
    extra_args <- arg_names[!is.element(arg_names, allowed_args)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    16x
                    
                      
    if (length(extra_args) == 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    4x
                    
                      
      return(invisible(NULL))

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    12x
                    
                      
    message <- paste(length(extra_args), "total unused argument(s).")

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    12x
                    
                      
    named_extra_args <- extra_args[!vapply(extra_args, identical, logical(1), "")]

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    12x
                    
                      
    if (length(named_extra_args) > 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    9x
                    
                      
      message <- paste0(

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    9x
                    
                      
        message,

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      
        " ",

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    9x
                    
                      
        length(named_extra_args),

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    9x
                    
                      
        " with name(s): ",

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    9x
                    
                      
        paste(named_extra_args, collapse = ", "),

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
        "."

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      
      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    12x
                    
                      
    if (stop) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    8x
                    
                      
      stop(message)

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    
                    
                      
    } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    4x
                    
                      
      warning(message)

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    
                    
                      
}

#' Whether the variable name is good to use within Show R Code

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    
                    
                      
#' Spaces are problematic because the variables must be escaped with backticks.

  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    92

#' Combine calls by operator

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

calls_combine_by <- function(calls, operator) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    56x
                    
                      
  checkmate::assert_list(calls)

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    49x
                    
                      
  if (length(calls) > 0L) checkmate::assert_list(calls, types = c("call", "name"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    55x
                    
                      
  checkmate::assert_string(operator)

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    53x

                    31
                    53x

                    32
                    53x
                    
                      
    x = calls,

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    53x
                    
                      
    f = function(x, y) call(operator, x, y)

  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
}

#' Topological graph sort

                    		
                  

                  

                    244
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    245
                    
                    
                      
#' Graph is a list which for each node contains a vector of child nodes

                    		
                  

                  

                    246
                    
                    
                      
#' in the returned list, parents appear before their children.

                    		
                  

                  

                    247
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    248
                    
                    
                      
#' Implementation of Kahn algorithm with a modification to maintain the order of input elements.

                    		
                  

                  

                    249
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    250
                    
                    
                      
#' @param graph (named `list`) list with node vector elements

#' @keywords internal

                    		
                  

                  

                    252
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    253
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    254
                    
                    
                      
#' \dontrun{

                    		
                  

                  

                    255
                    
                    
                      
#' topological_sort(list(A = c(), B = c("A"), C = c("B"), D = c("A")))

                    		
                  

                  

                    256
                    
                    
                      
#' topological_sort(list(D = c("A"), A = c(), B = c("A"), C = c("B")))

                    		
                  

                  

                    257
                    
                    
                      
#' topological_sort(list(D = c("A"), B = c("A"), C = c("B"), A = c()))

                    		
                  

                  

                    258
                    
                    
                      
#' }

                    		
                  

                  

                    259
                    
                    
                      
topological_sort <- function(graph) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    260
                    
                    
                      
  # compute in-degrees

                    		
                  

                  

                    261
                    73x
                    
                      
  in_degrees <- list()

                    		
                  

                  

                    262
                    73x
                    
                      
  for (node in names(graph)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    263
                    113x
                    
                      
    in_degrees[[node]] <- 0

                    		
                  

                  

                    264
                    113x
                    
                      
    for (to_edge in graph[[node]]) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    265
                    11x
                    
                      
      in_degrees[[to_edge]] <- 0

                    		
                  

                  

                    266
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    267
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    268
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    269
                    73x
                    
                      
  for (node in graph) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    270
                    113x
                    
                      
    for (to_edge in node) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    271
                    11x
                    
                      
      in_degrees[[to_edge]] <- in_degrees[[to_edge]] + 1

                    		
                  

                  

                    272
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    273
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    274
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    275
                    
                    
                      
  # sort

                    		
                  

                  

                    276
                    73x
                    
                      
  visited <- 0

                    		
                  

                  

                    277
                    73x
                    
                      
  sorted <- list()

                    		
                  

                  

                    278
                    73x
                    
                      
  zero_in <- list()

                    		
                  

                  

                    279
                    73x
                    
                      
  for (node in names(in_degrees)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    280
                    102x
                    
                      
    if (in_degrees[[node]] == 0) zero_in <- append(zero_in, node)

                    		
                  

                  

                    281
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    282
                    73x
                    
                      
  zero_in <- rev(zero_in)

                    		
                  

                  

                    283
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    284
                    73x
                    
                      
  while (length(zero_in) != 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    285
                    110x
                    
                      
    visited <- visited + 1

                    		
                  

                  

                    286
                    110x
                    
                      
    sorted <- c(zero_in[[1]], sorted)

                    		
                  

                  

                    287
                    110x
                    
                      
    for (edge_to in graph[[zero_in[[1]]]]) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    288
                    8x
                    
                      
      in_degrees[[edge_to]] <- in_degrees[[edge_to]] - 1

                    		
                  

                  

                    289
                    8x
                    
                      
      if (in_degrees[[edge_to]] == 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    290
                    8x
                    
                      
        zero_in <- append(zero_in, edge_to, 1)

                    		
                  

                  

                    291
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    292
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    293
                    110x
                    
                      
    zero_in[[1]] <- NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    294
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    295
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    296
                    73x
                    
                      
  if (visited != length(in_degrees)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    297
                    1x
                    
                      
    stop(

                    		
                  

                  

                    298
                    1x
                    
                      
      "Graph is not a directed acyclic graph. Cycles involving nodes: ",

                    		
                  

                  

                    299
                    1x
                    
                      
      paste0(setdiff(names(in_degrees), sorted), collapse = " ")

                    		
                  

                  

                    300
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    301
                    
                    
                      
  } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    302
                    72x
                    
                      
    return(sorted)

                    		
                  

                  

                    303
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    304
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                
              

            

            

              

                
                  

                    1
                    
                    
                      
#' Progress bars with labels

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' `shiny` element showing progress bar counts. Each element can have an

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' unique `id` attribute so each can be used independently.

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' Progress bar size is dependent on the ratio `choicesnow[i] / countsmax[i]`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' Label is `choices[i] (countsnow[i]/countsmax)`

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' @param session (`session`) object passed to function given to `shinyServer`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' @param inputId (`character(1)`) `shiny` id

                    		
                  

                  

                    9

#' @details

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' This class is responsible for managing single filter item within

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' `FilteredData` class. Filter states depend on the variable type:

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#' (`logical`, `integer`, `numeric`, `factor`, `character`, `Date`, `POSIXct`, `POSIXlt`)

                    		
                  

                  

                    13

                    14

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#' code relevant to selected values.

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#' - `factor`, `character`: `class = ChoicesFilterState`

                    		
                  

                  

                    17

                    18

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#' - `Date`: `class = DateFilterState`

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#' - `POSIXct`, `POSIXlt`: `class = DatetimeFilterState`

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#' - all `NA` entries: `class: FilterState`, cannot be filtered

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#' - default: `FilterState`, cannot be filtered

                    		
                  

                  

                    23

                    24

                    25

                    28

                    30

#' \cr

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
#' @section Modifying state:

                    		
                  

                  

                    33

                    34
                    
                    
                      
#' * In the interactive session by passing an appropriate `teal_slice`

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
#'   to the `set_state` method, or using

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
#'   `set_selected`, `set_keep_na` or `set_keep_inf` methods.

#' @title `FilterStates` R6 class

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' @description

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' Abstract class that manages adding and removing `FilterState` objects

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' and builds a \emph{subset expression}.

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' A `FilterStates` object tracks all subsetting expressions

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' (logical predicates that limit observations) associated with a given dataset

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' and composes them into a single reproducible R expression

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' that will assign a subset of the original data to a new variable.

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' This expression is hereafter referred to as \emph{subset expression}.

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' The \emph{subset expression} is constructed differently for different

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' classes of the underlying data object and `FilterStates` subclasses.

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#' Currently implemented for `data.frame`, `matrix`,

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#' `SummarizedExperiment`, and `MultiAssayExperiment`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#' @keywords internal

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
FilterStates <- R6::R6Class( # nolint

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
  classname = "FilterStates",

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
  # public members ----

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
  public = list(

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
    #' @description

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
    #' Initializes `FilterStates` object.

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
    #'

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
    #' Initializes `FilterStates` object by setting

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
    #' `dataname`, and `datalabel`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
    #'

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param data (`data.frame`, `MultiAssayExperiment`, `SummarizedExperiment`, `matrix`)\cr

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
    #'   the R object which `subset` function is applied on.

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param data_reactive (`function(sid)`)\cr

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
    #'   should return an object of the same type as `data` object or `NULL`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
    #'   This object is needed for the `FilterState` counts being updated

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
    #'   on a change in filters. If function returns `NULL` then filtered counts are not shown.

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
    #'   Function has to have `sid` argument being a character.

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param dataname (`character(1)`)\cr

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
    #'   name of the data used in the expression

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
    #'   specified to the function argument attached to this `FilterStates`

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param datalabel (`NULL` or `character(1)`)\cr

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      
    #'   text label value

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
    #'

                    		
                  

                  

                    44

    #' @description

                    		
                  

                  

                    217
                    
                    
                      
    #' Returns reproducible condition call for current selection.

                    		
                  

                  

                    218
                    
                    
                      
    #' For this class returned call looks like

                    		
                  

                  

                    219
                    
                    
                      
    #' `<varname> >= <min value> & <varname> <= <max value>` with

                    		
                  

                  

                    220
                    
                    
                      
    #' optional `is.na(<varname>)` and `is.finite(<varname>)`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    221
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param dataname name of data set; defaults to `private$dataname`

                    		
                  

                  

                    222
                    
                    
                      
    #' @return (`call`)

    #'

    get_call = function(dataname) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    225
                    41x
                    
                      
      if (isFALSE(private$is_any_filtered())) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    226
                    5x
                    
                      
        return(NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    227
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    228
                    4x

                    36x

                    230
                    36x

                    231
                    
                    
                      
          "&",

                    		
                  

                  

                    232
                    36x

                    233
                    36x

                    234
                    
                    
                      
        )

                    		
                  

                  

                    235
                    36x

                    236
                    
                    
                      
    },

                    		
                  

                  

                    237
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    238
                    
                    
                      
    #' @description

                    		
                  

                  

                    239
                    
                    
                      
    #' Returns current `keep_inf` selection

                    		
                  

                  

                    240
                    
                    
                      
    #' @return (`logical(1)`)

    get_keep_inf = function() {

                    !

  ),

                    258
                    118x

                    118x

                    1x

DFFilterStates <- R6::R6Class( # nolint

                    		
                  

                  

                    125
                    
                    
                      
  classname = "DFFilterStates",

                    		
                  

                  

                    126
                    
                    
                      
  inherit = FilterStates,

                    		
                  

                  

                    127
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    128
                    
                    
                      
  # public methods ----

                    		
                  

                  

                    129
                    
                    
                      
  public = list(

                    		
                  

                  

                    130
                    
                    
                      
    #' @description Initializes `DFFilterStates` object.

                    		
                  

                  

                    131
                    
                    
                      
    #'

                    		
                  

                  

                    132
                    
                    
                      
    #' Initializes `DFFilterStates` object by setting `dataname`

                    		
                  

                  

                    133
                    
                    
                      
    #'  and initializing `state_list` (`shiny::reactiveVal`).

                    		
                  

                  

                    134
                    
                    
                      
    #' This class contains a single `state_list` with no specified name,

                    		
                  

                  

                    135
                    
                    
                      
    #' which means that when calling the subset function associated with this class

                    		
                  

                  

                    136
                    
                    
                      
    #' (`dplyr::filter`), a list of conditions is passed to unnamed arguments (`...`).

                    		
                  

                  

                    137
                    
                    
                      
    #'

                    		
                  

                  

                    138
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param data (`data.frame`)\cr

                    		
                  

                  

                    139
                    
                    
                      
    #'   the R object which `dplyr::filter` function is applied on.

                    		
                  

                  

                    140
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param data_reactive (`function(sid)`)\cr

                    		
                  

                  

                    141
                    
                    
                      
    #'   should return a `data.frame` object or `NULL`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    142
                    
                    
                      
    #'   This object is needed for the `FilterState` counts being updated

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    
                    
                      
    #'   on a change in filters. If function returns `NULL` then filtered counts are not shown.

                    		
                  

                  

                    144
                    
                    
                      
    #'   Function has to have `sid` argument being a character.

                    		
                  

                  

                    145
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param dataname (`character`)\cr

                    		
                  

                  

                    146
                    
                    
                      
    #'   name of the data used in the \emph{subset expression}

                    		
                  

                  

                    147
                    
                    
                      
    #'   specified to the function argument attached to this `FilterStates`

                    		
                  

                  

                    148
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param datalabel (`NULL` or `character(1)`)\cr

                    		
                  

                  

                    149
                    
                    
                      
    #'   text label value

                    		
                  

                  

                    150
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param keys (`character`)\cr

                    		
                  

                  

                    151
                    
                    
                      
    #'   key columns names

                    		
                  

                  

                    152
                    
                    
                      
    #'

                    		
                  

                  

                    153
                    
                    
                      
    initialize = function(data,

                    		
                  

                  

                    154
                    
                    
                      
                          data_reactive = function(sid = "") NULL,

                    		
                  

                  

                    155
                    
                    
                      
                          dataname,

                    		
                  

                  

                    156
                    
                    
                      
                          datalabel = NULL,

                    		
                  

                  

                    157
                    
                    
                      
                          keys = character(0)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    158
                    127x
                    
                      
      checkmate::assert_function(data_reactive, args = "sid")

                    		
                  

                  

                    159
                    127x
                    
                      
      checkmate::assert_data_frame(data)

                    		
                  

                  

                    160
                    127x
                    
                      
      super$initialize(data, data_reactive, dataname, datalabel)

                    		
                  

                  

                    161
                    127x
                    
                      
      private$keys <- keys

                    		
                  

                  

                    162
                    127x
                    
                      
      private$set_filterable_varnames(include_varnames = colnames(private$data))

                    		
                  

                  

                    163
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    164
                    
                    
                      
  ),

                    		
                  

                  

                    165
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    166
                    
                    
                      
  # private members ----

                    		
                  

                  

                    167
                    
                    
                      
  private = list(

                    		
                  

                  

                    168
                    
                    
                      
    fun = quote(dplyr::filter)

                    		
                  

                  

                    169
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    170
                    
                    
                      
)

                    		
                  

                
              

            

            

              

                
                  

                    1
                    
                    
                      
#' Initializes `FilteredDataset`

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' @keywords internal

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
